modules.description: Provides functions to parse and evaluate arithmetic expressions, handling integers and binary operations. Works with abstract syntax trees and token streams generated from user input. Enables real-time feedback during interactive coding exercises.

Provides a function to execute applications with a specific signature, taking an app value and returning unit. It operates on custom app types defined within the platform's domain. Used to launch interactive environments or simulations with predefined configurations.

This library provides animation functions for generating dynamic visual effects through time-based numeric transformations, along with tools for creating and manipulating graphical shapes like polygons and images. It includes input handling mechanisms that convert keyboard commands into movement values, enabling interactive game scenes and responsive visual compositions using coordinates, colors, and transformation operations.
